#- ░ §0§lExec Summary§0
§0
§0Atrophy is named after the phenomenon of players who become regularly or permanently inactive, stagnating settlements in Civcraft to the point of total degeneration and 
#- abandonment.§0
§0
§0There are now more than 178 areas of the map affected by Atrophy, spread across all four quadrants.§0
§0
§0Atrophy continues to confound the scientific community, resisting even the
#- most desperate reversal efforts in severely affected regions.§0
§0
§0We now know that not only does Atrophy cause permanent inactivity (death) of individual players, but it can also close entire cities and shut down regional economies.
#- 
§0
§4Player contact with§0
§4Atrophic zones is§0
§4extremely toxic and§0
§4often fatal.§0
§0
§4§lExposure should§0
§4§lbe avoided!
#- Atrophy appears to be spreading by direct and indirect means of conveyance, which are in most cases connected to the actions (or inactions) of players, with the remainder of instances attributable to the server’s own forces of nature.
#- There is currently no known cure for Atrophy; however prescribed treatment plans may provide temporary relief in some cases.
